I reduced the amount of lemon. Thought it might be too lemony and I liked it as I did it. Lemon is strong and tends to overpower a mild flavor like pork tenderloin. I added some artichoke quarters and made more sauce than would result from the recipe as stated, thickening it with corn starch in sherry. Wonderful recipe. The capers were great. I think I will try it again and see if green peppercorns are a nice variation.

