Rating: 2
I think this kind of sauce is nicer on pounded, floured chicken breasts. I did double the sauce, as others recommend. I also substituted a little white wine for some of the broth, added finely grated lemon zest, and served with lots of italian parsley. I found it a bit tart and forgot that usually I add a little bit of sugar to this kind of sauce. My whole family ate it up, but I think I'd go back to chicken next time -- somehow pork has much better companions than capers.

