Rating: 3
When I serve this for a dinner party for 8, I saute 4 whole tenderloins in 2 tablespoons oil and 3 tablespoons butter until brown on all sides,transfer to shallow baking dish and bake for 20-30 minutes until thermometer registers 155. While pork is roasting, I make the sauce and then add the pork juices after slicing. I agree with other reviews that "the more sauce the better."

